                        "name": "3.A.2 Number of dentists per 10 thous. population (employed persons in the main place of work)",
                      
                        "goal": "Goal 3. Good health and well-being",
                      
                        "priority": "Increasing access to public health services",
                      
                        "definition": "Number of dentists (working according to their primary place of work) per 10 thousand people.",
                      
                        "unit": "persons",
                      
                        "dimensions": "total",
                      
                        "methodology": "A dentist is a medical profession that involves the provision of health services in the field of diseases of the teeth, oral cavity, facial part of the skull and adjacent areas by a person with the required qualifications, confirmed by appropriate documents. The regional medical council grants the right to practice medicine to a person who has obtained the required qualifications, completed a postgraduate internship and passed the Medical-Dental State Examination.Employed according to the primary place of work are people working full-time, in hours exceeding full-time and part-time in relation to the working time specified in the applicable regulations for a given type of work. These people, regardless of the working time, are counted once, according to the primary place of employment.",
                      
